items.content:
New comic!
Today's News:

Ahhh, light horror... there's nothing I love more... besides TAYLOR C., MY PARTNER IN LIFE AND CRIME AND THE INCREDIBLY TALENTED CREATOR OF MONSTERKIND AND ALSO THIS GUEST COMIC! Nothing makes me more proud of my work than Taylor's affection for it, so having her take a shine to DJ Mothman and Professor Bigfoot as their arc progressed is the biggest loveliest treat! Thanks, Taylor, you're the best! <3

After this... I take another week to do more prep and freelance... and then Chapter 7 starts on April 3rd!! I can't wait, it's a real juicy one, I hope you're as excited for it as I am!

items.creator: tech@thehiveworks.com
items.title: Paranatural - Chapter 6 Page 49
items.author: tech@thehiveworks.com
items.content:
New comic!
Today's News:

That's it, folks... the end of chapter six. I have to say, it's the most fun I've had with Paranatural in forever, thanks to the more manageable length and update schedule, the departure from the main cast in Stephen, and all of your continuous enthusiasm. I'm leaving this chapter feeling completely energized for the next one, which is new and so so nice! If you enjoyed this chapter and want to see me keep making more and better work, please consider supporting Paranatural on Patreon! I'm very excited for stuff I have going on in the background that will start trickling out there real soon.

OK, here's what's next: I have an illustration planned for the next update, and then my partner Taylor wants to do a DJ Mothman/Professor Bigfoot-centric guest comic the week after that... and then I'll be taking two weeks off to dive into freelance and planning out chapter seven in detail! After that... it's chapter seven time! Lemme do the calendar math real quick... OK, that means Paranatural returns with chapter seven on April 3rd! I'm VERY excited for this next one... and I'm pretty sure all of you will be too! I hope you'll check back for the illustration and guest comic until then! >:3

That's all for this post-chapter round-up, I'm gonna run (collapse)! As always, thank you so much for your support... and thanks for reading!!
